==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Occiput
<hw>Oc"ci*put</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> L.
<plw>Occipita</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, E. <plw>Occiputs</plw>.</plu>
<ety>[L., fr. <ets>ob</ets> (see <er>Ob-</er>) + <ets>caput</ets> head.
See <er>Chief</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>The back,
or posterior, part of the head or skull; the region of the occipital
bone.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A plate which forms the back part
of the head of insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Occision</ent>⟦br⟧
